  "text": "Patient safety culture is the \"values shared among members of the organization on what they think as important, their beliefs about how things operate in the organization, and the interaction of these with work unit and organizational structures and systems, which together produce behavioral norms in the organization that promote safety\" (Singer, Lin, Falwell, Gaba, & Baker, 2009, p. 400) . In addition, patient safety culture integrates communication and teamwork, acknowledges mutual dependency, and emphasizes the function of interpersonal work unit and organizational contributions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
